    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>KOREAN AIR STRIKE THREAT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Samuel Len</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Len, Samuel</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Pilots of Korean Air threaten to strike; claim that they are forced to fly too many hours (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Despite $200 million spent over the last three years by Korean Air to upgrade safety, pilots are threatening to strike, saying the airline is unsafe because they are forced to fly too many hours. The strike vote will continue into this weekend, and if the results favor a strike, the 1,330 unionized pilots plan to walk off their jobs at 6 a.m. Sunday.</p>
        <p>Samuel Len (NYT)</p>
      </block>
